{"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There are no steps needed to migrate to 1.19 of the Composable Architecture, but there are a number","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of changes and improvements that have been made to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Store"},{"text":" that one should be aware of.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Store internals rewrite","anchor":"Store-internals-rewrite","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The store’s internals have been rewritten to improved performance and to pave the way for future","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"features. While this should not be a breaking change, with any rewrite it is important to thoroughly","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"test your application after upgrading.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"StateObject compatibility","anchor":"StateObject-compatibility","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@State"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@StateObject"},{"type":"text","text":" allow a view to own a value or object over time, ensuring that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when a parent view is recomputed, the view-local state isn’t recreated from scratch."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One important difference between "},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"@StateObject","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is that "},{"code":"@State","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text",